description: This seminar series, meeting on the medical school campus, introduces students to leading figures in health care: public sector, private sector, and third sector executives and leaders discuss their career paths and current insights into the evolution and revolution in health care delivery and services. The course provides 0 credit in the fall term and 0.5 credit in the spring term for a full year of attendance. Only students who have been attending fall sessions can enroll in the spring.
